Parliament, Wednesday 30 October 2019 – President Cyril Ramaphosa will be in the National Assembly tomorrow, (Thursday, 31 October) for oral replies to questions by Members of Parliament. Section 92 (2) of the Constitution stipulates that Members of the Cabinet are accountable collectively and individually to Parliament for the exercise of the powers and the performance of their functions. The procedure for putting questions to the Executive is one of the instruments used by Parliament to hold the Executive accountable. DETAILS OF THE SITTING ARE AS FOLLOWS:
	DATE: Thursday, 31 October 2019
	TIME: 14.00
	VENUE: National Assembly Chamber, Parliament Questions to the President scheduled for tomorrow's sitting will cover a range of matters including what the current status of the cabinet’s discussions is relating to the proposed economy recovery plan of the Minister of Finance, Mr Tito Mboweni and by when the recovery plan will be tabled before Cabinet for a decision. For the list of questions in full please click:
	
